  "text": "In Beam v2.62.0, the former `runners/core-construction-java` module has been merged into `sdks/java/core` under `org.apache.beam.sdk.util.construction`. Key findings:\n\n1. **PipelineTranslator interface**: No standalone `PipelineTranslator` interface exists in core-java or core-construction. The pipeline-to-proto translation is handled by `PipelineTranslation` (sdks/java/core/.../construction/PipelineTranslation.java). Runner-specific `PipelineTranslator` interfaces exist in runners like Spark.\n\n2. **TransformHierarchy walker**: `TransformHierarchy` (sdks/java/core/.../runners/TransformHierarchy.java) manages the DAG of PTransform nodes and provides the visitor/walker pattern for traversing the pipeline graph.\n\n3. **PTransformOverride mechanism**: Composed of `PTransformOverride` (pairs a matcher with a factory), `PTransformOverrideFactory` (creates replacement transforms), `PTransformMatcher` (matches transforms to override), `PTransformMatchers` (common matcher implementations), `SingleInputOutputOverrideFactory`, `ReplacementOutputs`, `UnsupportedOverrideFactory`, and `ProtoOverrides` (proto-level overrides for portable pipelines).\n\n4. **ExecutableStagePayload construction**: `ExecutableStage` interface and `ImmutableExecutableStage` implementation define fused stages. `ExecutableStageTranslation` converts them to `ExecutableStagePayload` proto. `GreedyPipelineFuser` fuses pipeline graphs into executable stages.\n\n5. **BoundedSource/UnboundedSource adapters**: `BoundedReadFromUnboundedSource` (sdks/java/core/.../io/) wraps an unbounded source as bounded, and `UnboundedReadFromBoundedSource` (sdks/java/core/.../construction/) wraps a bounded source as unbounded. In runners/core-java, `SplittableParDoViaKeyedWorkItems` and `GroupByKeyViaGroupByKeyOnly` translate high-level transforms into runner primitives.",
